  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food safety remote inspection practices for improved trade</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. With the COVID-19 crisis, competent authorities and food safety service providers started to deploy remote inspection practices in food safety to fulfil their regulatory responsibilities and avoid any further disruption in existing food value chains; 2. STDF has approached UNIDO during the Working Group meeting in October 2020 to develop an initiative in order to identify potential best practices and solutions in remote inspection of food safety; 3. After the development of initial proposal, UNIDO was advised to focus on the identification of international best practices contributing to a future Codex Alimentarius project document. In addition, the reconsideration of pilot country(ies) was recommended due to the fact that the respective food control system need to have a certain development stage (updated regulatory and institutional framework in place). 4. Based on point 3, STDF has committed USD 50,000 for the normative work to identify international best practices and identify pilot country(ies) following a structured methodology for selection.</narrative>
  </description>
